Create an HTML/XHTML document to generate the following
(i) Unordered List (ii) Ordered List (iii) Definition List
*All the lists to contain at least 5 items




<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>HTML Lists Example</title>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Unordered List -->
    <h2>Unordered List - Fruits</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Apple</li>
        <li>Banana</li>
        <li>Mango</li>
        <li>Orange</li>
        <li>Grapes</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Ordered List -->
    <h2>Ordered List - Colors</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Red</li>
        <li>Blue</li>
        <li>Green</li>
        <li>Yellow</li>
        <li>Purple</li>
    </ol>

    <!-- Definition List -->
    <h2>Definition List - Programming Languages</h2>
    <dl>
        <dt>HTML</dt>
        <dd>HyperText Markup Language used to create the structure of web pages.</dd>

        <dt>C</dt>
        <dd>A general-purpose programming language used for system and application development.</dd>

        <dt>C++</dt>
        <dd>An object-oriented programming language developed as an extension of C.</dd>

        <dt>Java</dt>
        <dd>A platform-independent programming language used for web, mobile, and desktop applications.</dd>

        <dt>Python</dt>
        <dd>A high-level programming language known for its simple syntax and wide range of applications.</dd>
    </dl>
</body>
</html>




















Create, test, and validate a HTML document to describe a table with the following contents: 
The columns of the table must have the headings : Pine, Maple, Oak, and Fir. 
The rows must have the labels : Average Height, Average Width, Typical Lifespan, and Leaf Type. 
You can make up the data cell values.


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Tree Information Table</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h2>Tree Information Table</h2>

    <table border="1" cellpadding="8" cellspacing="0">
        <tr>
            <th>Characteristics</th>
            <th>Pine</th>
            <th>Maple</th>
            <th>Oak</th>
            <th>Fir</th>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <th>Average Height</th>
            <td>25 m</td>
            <td>20 m</td>
            <td>30 m</td>
            <td>35 m</td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <th>Average Width</th>
            <td>8 m</td>
            <td>10 m</td>
            <td>15 m</td>
            <td>7 m</td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <th>Typical Lifespan</th>
            <td>150 years</td>
            <td>100 years</td>
            <td>250 years</td>
            <td>180 years</td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <th>Leaf Type</th>
            <td>Needle</td>
            <td>Broadleaf</td>
            <td>Broadleaf</td>
            <td>Needle</td>
        </tr>

    </table>

</body>
</html>


















